• Editor’s note: This livestream has ended. You may watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng government's memorial service to honour the late poet and activist Professor Keorapetse Kgositsile took at the Johannesburg City Hall on Thursday. Kgositsile (79) died last week. READ: ‘Bra Willie’ memorial services begin Among those who paid tribute to the icon are poet Lebo Mashile, veteran actor and friend John Kani as well as rapper Khuli Chana. Another memorial service will be held at noon on Friday at Johannesburg's Market Theatre. eNCA